(a)  has  been  found  guilty  by  a  court  of  law  of  any  offence 
involving dishonesty, misuse or misappropriation of any 
money or property of a client or of any other person;

(b)  has been disbarred, struck off, suspended, reprimanded or 
censured in his capacity as a legal practitioner in any other 
country;

(c)  is the subject of a complaint concerning any dishonest act 
committed  by  him  in  his  capacity  as  an  advocate  and 
solicitor;

(a)  determines that the application or complaint be dismissed 
under paragraph 100(1)(a) or (3)(a) or subsection 103D(1); 
and

(a)  the Chief Judge or a Judge of the High Court nominated 
by the Chief Judge (in this section referred to as “the Chief 
Judge or his nominee”);

(a)  if the bill when taxed is less by a sixth part than the bill 
delivered,  then  the  advocate  and  solicitor  shall  pay  the 
costs;

